On Education and Sharing Day, President Donald Trump proclaimed March 27, 2018, as a day to honor the life and legacy of Rabbi Menachem Mendel Schneerson. The proclamation acknowledges the power of education and values in helping young people achieve purpose and passion in life. Rabbi Schneerson believed in the potential of all individuals and dedicated his life to empowering young people through education, character development, and civic pride. He established academic and outreach centers worldwide to provide spiritual and material assistance to young minds. The proclamation calls upon government officials, educators, volunteers, and all Americans to observe the day with appropriate programs and activities.